<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language> en-US</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2023</copyright><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:00:45 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Hack left majority of UK voters' data exposed for over a year]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>英国选举委员会<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/privacy-policy/public-notification-cyber-attack-electoral-commission-systems"><ins>透露</ins></a>，约 4000 万选民的部分个人信息被暴露一年多。该机构负责监管该国<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-11-15-uk-electoral-online-election-ad-funding.html"><ins>的政党和选举财务</ins></a>以及选举，表示它是“复杂网络攻击”的目标。它于 2022 年 10 月首次检测到其网络上的可疑​​活动，但表示入侵者于 2021 年 8 月首次访问其系统。</p><p>犯罪者找到了进入选举委员会服务器的方法，该服务器托管着该机构的电子邮件和控制系统以及选举登记册的副本。向注册政党和无党派活动人士提供的捐款和贷款的详细信息不受影响，因为这些信息存储在单独的系统中。该机构不掌握匿名选民的详细信息或在英国境外注册的海外选民的地址。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>曝光的数据包括 2014 年至 2022 年间登记投票的英国居民以及登记为海外选民的姓名和地址。通过电子邮件和网络表格向委员会提供的信息也被暴露。</p><p>该委员会表示：“我们知道这些数据是可以访问的，但我们无法确定攻击者是否读取或复制了我们系统上保存的个人数据。”该机构向<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/08/08/electoral-commission-hack-40-million-uk-voters/"><em><ins>TechCrunch</ins></em></a>证实，此次攻击可能影响了约 4000 万选民。 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/elections/electoralregistration/bulletins/electoralstatisticsforuk/december2021"><ins>根据英国人口普查数据</ins></a>，2021年12月议会选举登记人数为4660万，地方政府选举登记人数为4880万。</p><p>选举委员会<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/privacy-policy/public-notification-cyber-attack-electoral-commission-systems/information-about-cyber-attack"><ins>表示，</ins></a>在披露黑客攻击事件之前，它必须采取多项措施。它必须封锁“敌对行为者”，分析违规的可能程度，并采取更多安全措施，以防止未来发生类似情况。</p><p>该机构表示，选举登记册中的数据有限，其中大部分已经进入公共领域。因此，官员们认为这些数据本身并不会对个人构成重大风险。然而，该机构警告说，这些信息“可能会与公共领域的其他数据结合起来，例如个人选择分享的数据，以推断行为模式或识别和分析个人。”</p><p>选举委员会还指出，此次袭击并未对英国选举安全造成影响。 “访问的数据不会影响人们登记、投票或参与民主进程的方式，”它说。 “它对选举登记册的管理或选举的进行没有影响。英国的民主进程非常分散，其关键方面仍然基于纸质文件和计票。这意味着很难使用网络- 影响进程的攻击。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/hack-left-majority-of-uk-voters-data-expose-for-over-a-year-150045052.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/hack-left-majority-of-uk-voters-data-exposed-for-over-a-year-150045052.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 36a61aa6-583c-4208-be47-26876581b0bd</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:00:45 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691506313</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T14:51:58+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Elections]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="2961" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/c8f8bc90-35f8-11ee-babe-2834c77da772" width="4473"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2961" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/c8f8bc90-35f8-11ee-babe-2834c77da772" width="4473"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - People queue at the entrance of a polling station in London, on May 6, 2021. Britain’s electoral watchdog said Friday, June 23, 2023 that about 14,000 people were prevented from voting in last month’s local elections because of a new law requiring voters to show photo identification. The Electoral Commission said 0.25% of people who went to polling stations were unable to cast ballots because they didn’t have the right ID, and “significantly more” than that likely did not show up at all. (AP Photo/Frank Augstein, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Britain Voter ID?]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why humans can't use natural language processing to speak with the animals]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>自古以来，我们一直想知道动物的内心深处到底在想什么。<em>杜立特博士的</em>才华在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.google.com/books/edition/Doctor_Dolittle/ddcKgd_MWSwC?hl=en&amp;gbpv=1&amp;printsec=frontcover">1920 年首次出版时远非新颖。</a>希腊罗马文学<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://bmcr.brynmawr.edu/2021/2021.06.03/">在动物语言方面表现不佳</a>，<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.britannica.com/event/Warring-States">战国时代的中国</a>作家通常将<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/13/7/654">语言归因于某些动物物种</a>，而且它们在印度、埃及、希伯来和美洲原住民的讲故事传统中也很流行。</p><p>即使在今天，流行的西方文化也玩弄着会说话的动物的想法，尽管通常是通过技术赋能的言语而不是超自然力量的镜头。 <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://headhuntersholosuite.fandom.com/wiki/Darwin"><em>Seaquest DSV</em></a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.syfy.com/syfy-wire/chosen-one-of-the-day-jones-the-cyberpunk-dolphin-in-johnny-mnemonic"><em>Johnny Mnemonic</em></a>中的海豚通过先进的翻译设备与双足同类进行交流， <em>Up</em>中的<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://pixar.fandom.com/wiki/Dug">Dug 狗</a>也是如此。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>我们已经拥有机器学习系统和自然语言处理器，可以将人类语音翻译成任意数量的现有语言，并且调整该过程<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/can-ai-unlock-the-secrets-of-animal-communication-170040760.html">以将动物叫声转换为人类可解释的信号</a>似乎并不是那么困难。然而，事实证明，在我们能够<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-05-23-animal-translation-technology-talk-to-me.html">与大自然对话</a>之前，我们还有更多的工作要做。</p><h2>什么是语言？</h2><p> “所有生物都会进行交流，”一个跨学科研究小组在 2018 年的<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.bio.purdue.edu/People/faculty/lucas/2019.Freeberg%20et%20al.ANBEHAV.pdf"><em>《论理解社会认知的本质和进化：交流研究的必要性》一书中</em></a>指出。 “沟通涉及一个人的一种行为或特征，它以一种通常对两者都适用的方式影响至少另一个人的行为、行为倾向或生理。”</p><p>从<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/ele.12115">微生物、真菌和植物</a>到进化阶梯，科学尚未找到一种存在于如此极端孤立的生物体，以至于没有与周围世界沟通的自然方式。但我们应该清楚，“交流”和“语言”是两个截然不同的东西。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.linguisticsociety.org/resource/faq-how-did-language-begin">美国语言学会</a>认为，“没有其他自然交流系统能像人类语言一样”。语言可以让我们表达内心的想法、传递信息，也可以请求甚至要求。 “与任何其他动物通讯系统不同，它包含否定的表达——事实并非如此……相比之下，动物通讯系统通常最多有几十种不同的叫声，它们仅用于传达紧急问题，例如食物、危险、威胁或和解。”</p><p>这并不是说宠物不理解我们。俄勒冈州立大学人与动物互动实验室主任 Monique Udell 博士告诉 Engadget：“我们知道，当狗和猫之前有过对这些单词和相关结果的体验时，它们可以对各种人类单词做出准确的反应。” 。乌德尔博士说：“在许多情况下，这些关联是通过基本条件反射习得的。”就像我们在端上碗里的食物之前大喊“开饭了”一样。</p><p>除了直接的巴甫洛夫反应之外，我们的狗和猫是否真正理解“晚餐”的含义还有待观察。 “我们知道，至少有一些狗已经能够学会对 1,000 多个人类单词（物体的标签）做出高精度的反应，”乌德尔博士说。 “目前，狗在非人类动物物种中保持着能够将人类口语与物体或动作可靠匹配的记录，”但“很难确定狗在多大程度上理解我们的言语或行为背后的意图。”</p><p>乌德尔博士继续说道：“这是因为当我们测量狗或猫对刺激（例如单词）的理解时，我们通常会根据它们的行为来进行测量。”你可以用英语和德语命令教狗坐下，但是“如果狗在英语和德语中对‘坐’这个词的反应相同，那么可能是最简单的解释——最少的假设——是它们我们知道，当他们坐在任何一个词面前时，都会产生令人愉快的结果。” </p><figure><img src="https://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/midas/ef915e841ebc0fa3537d17abbd4023a/206377384/dog.png" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" data-uuid="c4d3c859-ebfb-3061-96c6-70bb293ea3e9"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Tea Stražičić 为 Engadget/Silica 杂志拍摄</div></figure><h2>安静，计算机正在说话</h2><p>自然语言编程 (NLP) 是人工智能的一个分支，它使计算机和算法模型能够解释文本和语音，包括说话者的意图，就像我们肉袋一样。它结合了计算语言学和机器学习模型，计算语言学对语言的句法、语法和结构进行建模，机器学习模型“自动提取、分类和标记文本和语音数据的元素，然后为这些元素的每个可能含义分配统计可能性”。元素”，<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.ibm.com/topics/natural-language-processing">根据 IBM 的说法</a>。 NLP 支撑着市场上每个数字助理的功能。基本上，每当您在“智能”设备上讲话时，NLP 都会将您的单词翻译成机器可理解的信号，<em>反之亦然</em>。</p><p> NLP研究领域近年来经历了重大演变，其核心系统已从较旧的循环神经网络和卷积神经网络迁移到<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://ai.googleblog.com/2017/08/transformer-novel-neural-network.html">谷歌的Transformer架构</a>，这大大提高了训练效率。</p><p>斯坦福大学心理学、计算机科学和语言学副教授 Noah D. Goodman 博士告诉 Engadget，使用 RNN，“你必须一步一步地或逐字地浏览数据”然后向后做同样的事情。”相比之下，使用变压器，“你基本上可以获取整个字符串并同时将它们推送到网络中。”</p><p> “提高培训效率确实很重要，”古德曼博士继续说道。 “变形金刚，它们很酷……但到目前为止，最重要的是它们使有效训练成为可能，因此可以在更多数据上训练更大的模型。”</p><h2>谈论 jive 不只是火鸡的专利</h2><p>尽管近年来许多物种的交流系统都得到了研究——最著名的是<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.projectceti.org/">鲸鱼</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.dolphincommunicationproject.org/">海豚</a>等鲸目动物，还有<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.pnas.org/doi/10.1073/pnas.1600970113">南方花鹛</a>的歌声潜在的句法质量，以及<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Nature Research;elmt:;cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=c6c965be-a8ea-473d-89f4-9754f2675a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Nature+Research&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAR-MRlH5kg4o8BJDl7OlahRnXIKf_fJdn4F-E89GsNzx&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Fscitable%2Fknowledge%2Flibrary%2Fan-introduction-to-animal-communication-23648715%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">黑长尾猴的公共捕食者警告系统</a>——但没有一个物种表现出绝对的程度。复杂性就像<a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.americanscientist.org/article/the-complex-call-of-the-carolina-chickadee">鸟类家族 Paridae 的称呼</a>：山雀、山雀和山雀。</p><p>普渡大学生物科学系教授杰弗里·卢卡斯博士告诉 Engadget，Paridae 的叫声“是我们所知的最复杂的发声系统之一。归根结底，[该领域的大量研究]论文所表明的是它非常复杂，而这些论文的问题在于它们严重低估了[这些调用]实际上有多么复杂。”</p><p>这些鹦鹉通常生活在社会复杂的异种群体中，包括多种鸣禽和啄木鸟物种的混合群体。卢卡斯博士说，鸟类社会系统的复杂性与通讯系统多样性的增加相关。 “这种相关性存在的部分原因是，如果你有一个多维的复杂社会系统，那么你必须在不同的环境中传达各种不同类型的信息。在鸟类世界中，它们必须<a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.washington.edu/news/2005/06/23/chickadees-alarm-calls-carry-information-about-size-threat-of-predator/">保卫自己的领地</a>，谈论食物，融入社会体系[并解决]交配问题。”</p><p>山雀的叫声由至少六个不同的音符组成，采用开放式的声音结构，这在非人类通信系统中极为罕见，也是山雀叫声复杂的原因。 2012 年的研究<a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3367703/"><em>《将社会复杂性与声音复杂性联系起来：平等的视角》</em></a>解释道，开放式发声系统意味着“增加对小鸡叫声的录音将不断揭示具有不同音符类型成分的叫声”。 “这种开放性是小鸡叫声与人类语言共有的主要特征之一，也是小鸡叫声与大多数鸣禽物种有限的鸣叫曲目之间的主要区别之一。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/df723400-35f4-11ee-8e7f-9a864f4822c7" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="Tea Stražičić 的海豚翻译" data-uuid="31f8b8c7-ac3a-360a-93e8-3b2621a7f9b2"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Tea Stražičić 为 Engadget/Silica 杂志拍摄</div></figure><h2>海豚不需要国王</h2><p>训练语言模型不仅仅是输入大量数据的问题。当训练模型将未知语言翻译成您所说的内容时，您至少需要对这两种语言如何相互关联有一个基本的了解，以便翻译后的文本保留说话者的正确意图。</p><p>古德曼博士解释说：“我们可以获得的最有力的数据就是所谓的平行语料库，”这基本上就是两个舌头的罗塞塔石碑。在这种情况下，您只需在每种语言中的特定单词、符号和音素之间进行映射 - 弄清楚每种语言中“河流”或“一蒲式耳小麦”的含义，然后从那里进行构建。</p><p>如果没有完美的翻译工件，只要你拥有两种语言的大量数据语料库，“仍然可以学习两种语言之间的翻译，但这非常关键地取决于潜在概念结构的种类，”博士说。古德曼继续说道，他假设两种文化对“一蒲式耳小麦”的定义通常是相同的。</p><p>古德曼指出英语中的“男人和女人”以及“国王和王后”这两个词对。 “我们期望英语中这种关系的结构或几何形状，如果我们翻译成匈牙利语，我们也会期望这四个概念处于类似的关系，”古德曼博士说。 “那么，我们现在学习翻译的有效方法就是学习以尽可能保留概念空间结构的方式进行翻译。”</p><p>古德曼博士说，在这种情况下，拥有大量数据可以使用无监督学习技术来“提取潜在的概念空间”，尽管这种方法资源密集且效率较低。但是，如果您拥有的只是其中一种语言的大型语料库，那么您通常会运气不好。</p><p> “对于大多数人类语言，我们假设[四重奏概念]有点相似，比如，也许它们没有‘国王和王后’，但它们肯定有‘男人和女人’，”古德曼博士继续说道。 “但我认为对于动物交流，我们不能假设海豚有‘国王和王后’的概念，或者它们是否有‘男人和女人’。我不知道，也许，也许不是。”</p><p>即使没有基本的概念一致性，辨别动物叫声的上下文和意图——更不用说破译底层通信系统的句法、语法和语义——变得更加困难。 “你的地位要弱得多，”古德曼博士说。 “如果你在世界语境中掌握了这些话语，那么你也许能够有所收获。”</p><p>基本上，如果您可以获得为记录的动物叫声提供上下文的多模态数据（环境条件、一天或一年中的时间、猎物或捕食者物种的存在等），您就可以将语言数据“扎根”到物理环境中。从那里你可以“假设英语扎根于物理环境，就像这种奇怪的新语言扎根于物理环境一样”，并将其用作语言之间的一种桥梁。</p><p>不幸的是，将鸟叫声翻译成英语（或任何其他人类语言）的挑战将完全属于第四类。这意味着我们将需要更多的数据和许多不同类型的数据，因为我们继续从头开始建立对这些调用结构的基本理解。其中一些努力已经在进行中。</p><p>例如，海豚通讯项目采用“<a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.dolphincommunicationproject.org/the-mva-and-ecd/">移动视频/声学系统</a>”组合来捕捉野生海豚的话语及其当时在物理空间中的相对位置，为研究人员提供更多的呼叫背景信息。生物记录标签——贴在动物皮毛、毛发或角上的传感器，用于追踪宿主的位置和状况—— <a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://royalsocietypublishing.org/doi/10.1098/rstb.2020.0229">尺寸不断缩小，但容量和能力不断增强</a>，这应该有助于研究人员收集更多有关这些群落的数据。</p><h2>如果鸟儿因为天气太热而不断尖叫怎么办？</h2><p>即使我们无法立即与毛茸茸的邻居聊天，更好地了解它们至少如何相互交谈也可能对保护工作有价值。卢卡斯博士指出，他最近参与的一项研究发现，气候变化引起的环境变化可以从根本上改变不同鸟类在混合群体中相互作用的方式。 “我们表明，如果你观察干扰梯度，那么一切都会改变，”卢卡斯博士说。 “它们在空间中所做的事情发生了变化，它们与其他鸟类互动的方式也发生了变化。他们的发声系统发生了变化。”</p><p> “冬季鸟类的社交互动非常重要，因为你知道，10 克重的鸟 - 如果它一天不吃东西，它就死了，”卢卡斯博士继续说道。 “因此，有关其环境的信息非常重要。这些混合物种羊群所做的就是提供一些信息。”</p><p>然而，随着栖息地的退化，这个网络很快就会崩溃，为了生存，“他们必须在行为、社会系统和声音系统上经历相当极端的变化……但这会影响生育率，以及他们养育孩子的能力等等的东西。”</p><p>更好地了解它们的叫声将有助于我们更好地了解它们的压力水平，这既可以服务于现代保护工作，也可以服务于农业目的。 “我们的想法是，我们可以了解[农场动物]的压力水平，然后将其用作谷仓中发生的情况的指标，以及我们是否可以通过发声来减轻压力，”卢卡斯博士说。 “人工智能可能会帮助我们做到这一点。”</p><p> “科学资料表明，农场动物环境中的噪音对动物健康有害，”尼特拉动物生产研究所的 Jan Brouček<a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="http://www.cvzv.sk/slju/14_2/8_Broucek.pdf">在 2014 年观察到</a>。 “尤其是持续时间较长的声音会影响动物的健康。噪音直接影响生殖生理或能量消耗。” <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fanim.2021.744207/full">人们认为，这种持续的无人机还会间接影响其他行为</a>，包括栖息地使用、求爱、交配、繁殖和照顾后代。</p><p>相反，2021 年的研究<a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8698046/"><em>《音乐对牲畜：牛、家禽和猪的影响》</em></a>表明，播放音乐有助于安抚牲畜并减轻集约生产期间的压力。我们可以根据<a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0168159121000514">这些动物发出的快乐声音</a>来衡量压力的减轻程度。就像听另一种语言的音乐一样，即使我们听不懂歌词，我们也能融入其中</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/why- humans-cant-use-natural-language-processing-to-speak-with-the-animals-143050169.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/why-humans-cant-use-natural-language-processing-to-speak-with-the-animals-143050169.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 839bef18-891f-4301-ac66-76977e614f3e</guid><dc:creator>安德鲁·塔兰托拉</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 14:30:50 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691504418</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T14:20:27+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Finance - Career & Education]]></category><category><![CDATA[Personal Investing Ideas & Strategies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Computer Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Biology]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Andrew Tarantola]]></category><media:content height="3840" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/310806a0-3541-11ee-baf7-fd5a418556a5" width="5760"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1719" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/20320740-3541-11ee-aff5-ea3407b04d28" width="3000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[C Flanigan via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[SAN FRANCISCO, CA - AUGUST 07:  Animal of Muppet Band Dr. Teeth & the Electric Mayhem performs during the 2016 Outside Lands Music And Arts Festival at Golden Gate Park on August 7, 2016 in San Francisco, California.  (Photo by C Flanigan/WireImage)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[2016 Outside Lands Music And Arts Festival - Day 3]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best Chromebooks you can buy in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>鉴于当今市场上的型号繁多，根据您的需求和预算选择最好的 Chromebook 可能很困难。多年的软件更新和笔记本电脑制造商制造出功能更强大、性能更好的笔记本电脑相结合，意味着有大量优秀的 Chrome 操作系统机器可以作为日常驱动程序正常工作。但在选择 Chromebook 之前，您应该牢记一些特殊因素。从 Lenovo IdeaPad Flex 5i 到 Acer Chromebook Spin 714，我们的首选将帮助您确定哪款 Chromebook 值得您购买。</p><h2>什么是 Chrome 操作系统？为什么我要在 Windows 上使用它？</h2><p>这可能是有关 Chromebook 的第一个问题。市场上有很多廉价的 Windows 笔记本电脑，那么为什么还要费心使用 Chrome 操作系统呢？很高兴你问了。对我来说，Chrome 操作系统的简单和干净的本质是一个很大的卖点。 Chrome 操作系统基于 Google 的 Chrome 浏览器，这意味着您可以运行的大多数程序都是基于网络的。没有像 Windows 笔记本电脑上常见的那样需要卸载臃肿软件或不需要的应用程序，它可以在几秒钟内启动，并且您几乎可以同样快地完全重置为出厂设置。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>当然，对于某些用户来说，简单性也是一个主要缺点。如果您是视频编辑器或软件开发人员，则无法安装本机软件可能会成为问题。但也有很多人在浏览器中完成大部分工作。但谷歌及其软件合作伙伴在支持更高级功能方面每年都在进步。例如，Google 在 Chromebook 上的 Google Photos 应用程序中<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://support.google.com/photos/thread/208682996/bring-your-creativity-to-life-with-photos%E2%80%99-new-video-editing-features-on-chromebook?hl=en">添加了视频编辑工具</a>- 它不会取代 Adob​​e Premiere，但对很多人来说应该很方便。</p><p>谷歌还增加了对 Chromebook 上 Android 应用程序的支持，这极大地扩展了可用软件的数量。质量差异很大，但这意味着您可以使用 Chromebook 做更多事情，而不仅仅是基于网络的应用程序。例如，您可以安装 Netflix 应用程序并保存视频以供离线观看。 Microsoft Office 和 Adob​​e Lightroom 等其他 Android 应用程序的功能也令人惊讶。在 Android 应用程序和网络应用程序的全面改进之间，Chromebook 不仅仅是一个浏览器。</p><h2> Chromebook 的优点是什么？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-08/38bdd2f0-2488-11ed-affd-31657bb03b0c" alt="三台 Chromebook 笔记本电脑叠放在一起，稍微呈扇形展开，放在木桌上的桌面保护罩上。" data-uuid="24972f7b-1262-3d93-8e2b-f189a92fda1b"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">内森·英格拉汉姆 / Engadget</div></figure><p>简而言之，网络浏览和任何基于网络的内容。浏览、流媒体音乐和视频以及使用各种社交媒体网站是人们在 Chromebook 上最常见的日常任务。正如您所料，它们还可以与照片、文档、Gmail、云端硬盘、Keep 等 Google 服务配合良好。是的，任何可以运行 Chrome 的计算机都可以做到这一点，但 Google Chrome 操作系统的轻量级特性使其成为一个响应灵敏且稳定的平台。</p><p>正如我之前提到的，Chrome 操作系统可以运行 Android 应用程序，因此如果您是 Android 用户，您会发现平台之间存在一些良好的联系。您可以在 Chromebook 上获取手机上的大多数相同应用程序，并保持它们之间的信息同步。您还可以使用某些 Android 手机作为 Chromebook 的安全密钥，或立即限制您的笔记本电脑使用移动数据。</p><p>谷歌继续将安全性视为 Chromebook 的主要差异化因素，我认为这绝对是一个值得考虑的因素。第一道防线是自动更新。 Chrome 操作系统更新可在后台快速下载，只需快速重启即可安装最新版本。谷歌表示，Chromebook 上的每个网页和应用程序也都在自己的沙箱中运行，因此任何安全威胁都包含在各个应用程序中。最后，Chrome 操作系统有一个名为“验证启动”的自检功能，每次设备启动时都会运行。除此之外，您通常无法在 Chromebook 上安装传统应用程序这一简单事实意味着不良行为者访问系统的方式要少得多。</p><p>至于何时避免它们，答案很简单：如果您严重依赖 Windows 或 Mac 的特定本机应用程序，那么您很可能在 Chromebook 上找不到完全相同的选项。在照片和视频编辑等领域尤其如此，但在法律或金融领域也可能如此。许多企业都在使用 Google 的 G 套件软件，但更多企业仍然有 Chromebook 可能无法满足的特定要求。如果您是 iPhone 用户，您还会错过 iPhone 与 iPad 或 Mac 轻松集成的方式。对我来说，最大的缺点是无法在 Chromebook 上访问 iMessage。</p><p>最后，游戏 Chromebook 并不是无处不在，尽管随着云游戏的兴起，它们正成为一个<em>稍微</em>更合理的选择。 2022 年底，谷歌和一些硬件合作伙伴宣布推动生产带有<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-cloud-gaming-chromebooks-asus-lenovo-acer-130030080.html">云游戏</a>功能的 Chromebook。从硬件角度来看，这意味着笔记本电脑具有更大的屏幕和更高的刷新率，并优化这些笔记本电脑以与 NVIDIA GeForce Now、Xbox Game Pass 和 Amazon Luna 等服务配合使用。显然，您需要互联网连接才能使用这些服务，但好消息是在 Chromebook 上玩现代游戏并非不可能。您可以从 Google Play 商店安装 Android 游戏，但这并不是大多数人想在笔记本电脑上玩游戏时想到的。</p><p>还有另一个潜在的变化即将出现，Valve 和 Google 正在努力将庞大的 Steam 目录引入 Chromebook。目前，Steam 仅在少数更高规格的设备上作为早期 alpha 版本提供，但它的运行效果比我预期的要好得多。当然，您仍然无法在基本笔记本电脑上运行要求最高的游戏，但 Steam 目录非常庞大，有很多游戏可以在我测试的 Chromebook 上运行。希望 Steam 很快能在更多设备上得到支持，<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/steam-on-chromeos/">但目前列表</a>有些有限。</p><h2> Chromebook 最重要的规格是什么？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-06/28c4bed0-cd37-11eb-a7ff-de290c52cdf7" alt="宏碁 Chromebook Spin 713" data-uuid="fc221c8a-c134-348a-a3e8-03c468c702c4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">内森·英格拉汉姆 / Engadget</div></figure><p> Chrome 操作系统是轻量级的，通常在相当普通的硬件上运行良好，因此最重要的事情可能不是处理器能力或存储空间。也就是说，我仍然建议您购买配备相对较新的英特尔处理器的 Chromebook，最好是第 10 代或更新的英特尔 i3。我尝试过的大多数非英特尔 Chromebook 都没有非常强大的性能，但这种情况正在开始改变 - 随着我们评估更多这些 Chromebook，我们将推荐那些具有足够功能的日常计算机。</p><p>至于 RAM，8GB 应该是目标，除非您正在寻找预算型号并且知道您的需求相当适中。储物空间是另一个你不需要花费太多的地方； 64GB 应该适合几乎任何人。如果您计划在本地存储大量文件或在 Chromebook 上加载 Linux 或 Android 应用程序，请选择 128GB。但无论如何，我在使用 Chrome 操作系统时从未感觉存储空间可能会耗尽。</p><p>键盘和显示屏质量等因素可以说比纯粹的规格更重要。好消息是，您可以找到更便宜的 Chromebook，但它们仍然具有相当好的屏幕和键盘，您不会介意整天打字。许多廉价 Chromebook 仍然配备微型、低分辨率显示屏，但目前没有理由满足于低于 1080p 的分辨率。 （不过，如果您正在寻找一款极其便携的 11 英寸 Chromebook，那么您最终可能会选择较小的屏幕。）显然，键盘质量有点主观，但有很多价格实惠的选择，可以提供强大的功能。打字经验。</p><p> Google 有针对 Chromebook 的自动更新政策，虽然这本身不是规范，但值得在购买前检查。基本上，Chromebook 自发布之日起大约六年内会自动定期进行软件更新（尽管具体情况因设备而异）。<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://support.google.com/chrome/a/answer/6220366?hl=en">此支持页面</a>列出了几乎所有 Chromebook 的自动更新到期日期，但一个好的经验法则是尽可能购买最新的计算机，以最大限度地获得支持。</p><h2>我应该花多少钱？</h2><p> Chromebook 一开始非常便宜，标价通常低于 300 美元。但随着它们变得更加主流，它们已经从本质上现代的上网本转变为您想要整天使用的笔记本电脑。因此，过去几年价格略有上涨。此时，如果您想要一名可靠的日常司机，您应该预计至少花费 400 美元。仍然有许多预算选项可能适合作为辅助设备，但可以作为全天、日常笔记本电脑的 Chromebook 价格会更高一些。</p><p>还有很多接近甚至超过 1,000 美元的高级 Chromebook，但我不建议花那么多钱。一般来说，这将为您带来更好的设计、更优质的材料、更强大的内部结构和额外的存储空间。当然，有时您也会为品牌付费。但是，我之前概述的规格通常就足够了。也就是说，如果钱不是问题，那么还有一些非常棒的选择。</p><p><strong>也可以看看：</strong></p><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-120008636.html"><strong>2023 年最佳笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-laptops-172033838.html"><strong>最佳游戏笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-2-in-1-laptops-173038508.html"><strong>2023 年最佳二合一笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-affordable-windows-laptops-123000512.html"><strong>最便宜的 Windows 笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li><li><p><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-laptops-for-students-130054631.html"><strong>最适合大学生的笔记本电脑</strong></a></p></li></ul><h2>最物超所值：Lenovo IdeaPad Flex 5i</h2><p><core-commerce id="c041afb984ff410098fa7151948cc5b7" data-type="product-list"></p><p>几年来，联想一直在生产一些最实惠的 Chromebook，而<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWR6WZjttzosh6Ce0d6Fpj3kauddLu2r8ficQD_ifAjY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLenovo-2-1-Chromebook-Computer%2Fdp%2FB09RNCN3YV%3Fth%3D1">IdeaPad Flex 5i</a>是一款经济实惠的笔记本电脑，它提供了您在基本 Chromebook 中所需的几乎所有功能。 13.3 英寸、1080p 触摸屏非常明亮且相当清晰；我希望它的宽高比高于 16:9，但这在 Chromebook 中很常见。这款 Lenovo Chromebook 运行第 11 代 Intel Core i3 处理器，包括 8GB RAM 和 128GB 存储空间。虽然处理器已经开始老化，但它仍然足以胜任大多数任务。对于这个价格范围内的笔记本电脑来说，八小时的电池续航时间已经相当不错了，而且背光键盘对于这种价格实惠的设备来说非常出色。键帽在我的手指下感觉有点小，但这是我唯一真正的抱怨。</p><p> Flex 5i 的其他优点包括它同时具有 USB-C 和 USB-A 端口、一个 microSD 卡插槽和一个安全锁。它重 3 磅，厚 0.66 英寸，并不是最轻或最薄的选择，但考虑到价格，它是完全合理的。最后，Flex 5i 将在 2029 年 6 月之前收到软件和安全更新，因此您可以购买这台计算机并在未来几年内享受保修服务。</p><p>最终，Ideapad Flex 5i 满足了许多 Chromebook 买家的需求，提供了在这个价位上很少见的质量和性能水平。也就是说，鉴于这款笔记本电脑已经上市一年多了，我们正在密切关注联想的替代产品，以及其他制造商发布的类似选项。</p><p> Lenovo Flex 5i 不再直接从 Lenovo 购买，但您通常可以在亚马逊上以 400 美元左右的价格找到它（在撰写本文时，其售价为 368 美元）。这是一个非凡的价值。</p><h2>升级选项：Acer Chromebook Spin 714</h2><p><core-commerce id="95f0b0e58f474f4d9f29d13316b97c4b" data-type="product-list"></p><p></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAX1QeRQ01eSgnQlMtotxLWXdsieMp9lLHwOn72xLOT_S&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAcer-Chromebook-2-Touchscreen-Built%2Fdp%2FB0BJH9LGK8">宏碁的 Chromebook Spin 714</a>长期以来一直是最好的优质 Chromebook 选项之一，今年的更新也不例外。这是对 2022 年型号的适度调整，但考虑到该计算机的性能，我毫无疑问推荐最新版本。我们还没有对其进行测试，但宏碁很快就会为我们提供评测模型。</p><p> Spin 714 配备 14 英寸、1900x1200 触摸屏。与大多数 Chromebook 上的 1080p 面板相比，这会产生更高的 16:10 宽高比。我非常喜欢更高的笔记本电脑屏幕，虽然它不像市场上少数 3:2 比例的 Chromebook 那样奢华，但它仍然是一块舒适且高品质的屏幕。</p><p>一项值得注意的新功能是 Spin 714 中包含的 2K 网络摄像头。在当今世界，我们的视频通话次数都超出了我们的预期，拥有一台不会让您陷入模糊状态的摄像头绝对是值得赞赏的。</p><p>至于其他硬件，第 13 代英特尔酷睿 i5 处理器对于大多数任务来说应该绰绰有余，而且 2022 年型号的键盘和触控板即使不是最好的，也很坚固。电池续航时间也是如此：我在日常工作中使用 Spin 714 的时间约为 7 个小时。这并不特殊，但与我在其他 i5 驱动的 Chromebook 上看到的情况一致。硬件方面还包括 8GB RAM 和 256GB 的存储空间。最新的 Spin 714 型号并未列在 Google 的支持页面上，但去年的型号的支持期限到 2030 年 6 月；最新型号的窗口期应持续到 2031 年 6 月。</p><p>另一个好处是它的硬件符合 Google 推荐的运行 Steam 的规格，因此游戏玩家可能想尝试一下，看看他们可以安装哪些游戏。</p><p>顾名思义，Spin 714 具有 360 度铰链，可让您在平板电脑模式下使用笔记本电脑。 I&#39;m not a fan of this convertible design – I don&#39;t know who wants to use a 3-plus pound tablet, but Acer did include a built-in stylus for handwriting notes or drawing in apps like the built-in Chrome Canvas.</p><p> The latest Spin 714 costs $700 – not an unreasonable price for a computer with these specs and built quality. For most people, the Lenovo model will be enough. But, if you&#39;re a serious multitasker, want a better display and keyboard, or just want a computer that&#39;ll last as long as possible, the Acer Spin 714 is easy to recommend. We&#39;ll update this guide once we receive our test model from Acer so we can give updated impressions, particularly on battery life.</p><h2> A good large-screen option: Acer Chromebook 516 GE</h2><p><core-commerce id="71a3b213e2744dcbbd780b3abc02d825" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Acer introduced the <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9BY2VyLUNocm9tZWJvb2stNTE2LUdFLWk1LTEyNDBQL2RwL0IwQlZWVEwzODg_dGg9MSZ0YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby0zci0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzFjYTM1NWUtYmUwNi0zYmEyLWE4NGEtM2U1NWExOWRiYzg0In0&amp;signature=AQAAAeMPwDw6u8YHqYCk03cgZETQzsbwwkoyPvHFf1lC0Mi_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAcer-Chromebook-516-GE-i5-1240P%2Fdp%2FB0BVVTL388%3Fth%3D1">Chromebook 516 GE</a> in the fall of 2022 as part of Google&#39;s push to make devices suitable for cloud gaming, but you don&#39;t need to be a gamer <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/acer-chromebook-516-ge-hands-on-preview-170011142.html">to appreciate this laptop</a> . For $650, you&#39;ll get a 16-inch display with a 2,560 x 1,600 resolution and a 120hz refresh rate. NVIDIA&#39;s GeForce now gaming service supports up to 4K visuals at 120hz on its Ultimate tier so you&#39;ll get to see those benefits. This laptop also supports Steam, yet another reason gamers might be interested in trying it. But even non-gamers should enjoy the 516 GE&#39;s crisp and clear screen and refined hardware.</p><p> It also includes Intel&#39;s 12th-gen Core i7 1240P processor, 8GB of RAM and 256 GB of storage. Given the laptop&#39;s size, it&#39;s good that Acer didn&#39;t skimp on ports here: there&#39;s an HDMI port, USB-C, USB-A, ethernet and a headphone jack. The keyboard has gamer-friendly LED lights that you can customize, but more importantly it&#39;s just a solid and comfortable keyboard, whether you&#39;re playing games or just typing up reports. The trackpad is large and responsive, as well.</p><p> The 516 GE only weighs 3.75 pounds too – pretty light for a laptop with a 16-inch screen. Between the powerful hardware, solid design, good trackpad and keyboard and great screen, anyone who wants a bigger Chromebook will likely be happy with this model. As for support, Google says the 516 GE will continue receiving updates until June of 2030.</p><h2> Honorable mention: HP Dragonfly Pro Chromebook</h2><p><core-commerce id="d51234aaaa91453e94b11f10e2170144" data-type="product-list"></p><p> If you just want the nicest Chromebook you can buy, with top-shelf specs and design, the $999 <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:HP Store;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=8a0e8870-4cf8-4bda-935c-af7c00c28e2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=HP+Store&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATmD35Ks726xdz2LVY7LDZXAS0u_pQiizwieyaJc96qW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hp.com%2Fus-en%2Fshop%2Fpdp%2Fhp-dragonfly-pro-chromebook-16gb-bk">HP Dragonfly Pro Chromebook</a> might meet your needs. For starters, the screen is an absolute stand out. It&#39;s a 14-inch, 2,560 x 1,600 touchscreen that maxes out at an extremely bright 1,200 nits.</p><p> The keyboard and trackpad, meanwhile, are probably the best I&#39;ve tested lately. The keyboard has an extremely satisfying clickiness when you&#39;re typing. It&#39;s no mechanical keyboard, but it felt reassuringly solid and there was no real adjustment period needed when I started banging away on this laptop. The large trackpad is excellent, with great responsiveness and a solid click. There&#39;s also a fingerprint reader so you can unlock the laptop without a password, another premium feature that I wish I saw in more Chromebooks.</p><p> From a specs perspective, the Dragonfly Pro includes a 12th-gen Core i5 i5-1235U processor – not the absolute latest, but plenty of power nonetheless. That&#39;s matched with 16GB of RAM and 256GB of storage, and I definitely noticed the extra RAM makes a difference in responsiveness across the board.</p><p> Other niceties include an 8-megapixel webcam, a shooter that exceeds what you&#39;ll find on most laptops, whether they&#39;re in this price range or not. HP did this without resorting to a huge bezel, either – the top bezel is thicker than the ones on the side, but not so much that the laptop feels unbalanced. And the Bang &amp; Olufsen quad speaker setup is shockingly good. With volume set to about 33 percent, the laptop was plenty loud to fill my office, and it was also fairly well balanced, with prominent bass, surprising stereo separation and clear highs. These are definitely some of the best laptop speakers I&#39;ve ever heard.</p><p> That said, there is a major caveat here. The HP Dragonfly Pro&#39;s battery life is poor — under 5 hours poor, which is very disappointing for a $999 laptop. It&#39;s bad enough that I went back and forth on recommending this device. People who don&#39;t travel a lot and do most of their work at their desk might not care, but in that case, why bother getting one of the thinnest and lightest Chromebooks out there?</p><p> The other downside is that you don&#39;t get a variety of ports here – just four USB-C, and no headphone jack. That&#39;s not a total dealbreaker, as I don&#39;t often find myself plugging much into my Chromebooks, but again it&#39;s definitely worth knowing.</p><p> This laptop is otherwise a total delight to use, as it is extremely well built, powerful and features a great keyboard and screen. I definitely wouldn&#39;t recommend it to everyone with these battery issues, but if you want one of the nicest Chromebooks you can buy and don&#39;t spend a ton of time away from a charger (and have plenty of disposable income), you&#39;ll probably enjoy the Dragonfly Pro.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-chromebooks-160054646.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-chromebooks-160054646.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 71ca355e-be06-3ba2-a84a-3e55a19dbc84</guid><dc:creator> Nathan Ingraham</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 14:15:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691504108</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T14:15:19+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[chromeos]]></category><category><![CDATA[chromebook]]></category><category><![CDATA[hp]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[google]]></category><category><![CDATA[commerce]]></category><category><![CDATA[samsung]]></category><category><![CDATA[feature]]></category><category><![CDATA[asus]]></category><category><![CDATA[bts2020]]></category><category><![CDATA[lenovo]]></category><category><![CDATA[laptops]]></category><category><![CDATA[gear]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicEquipment,Instruments&Components]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicsAccessories]]></category><category><![CDATA[OfficeElectronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology&Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Small Businesses]]></category><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-04/ab871810-96d5-11eb-b5fe-41c2db4984ea" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-04/ab871810-96d5-11eb-b5fe-41c2db4984ea" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Chromebook 2 laptop with its lid open sitting on a wooden table.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Chromebook 2]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kamado Joe Konnected Joe review: A highly versatile smart grill]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Typically, smart grills equal pellet grills. While pellet models played a key role in popularizing connected outdoor cooking, there are plenty of other options for controlling and monitoring things from the comforts of your living room. After introducing <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-10-25-harvard-barbecue-desora-kamado-joe-cinder-grills.html">a smart controller</a> for its ceramic grills in 2018, Kamado Joe released <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kamado-joe-pellet-joe-ceramic-smart-grill-specs-price-availability-201946770.html">its own connected pellet version</a> in 2020. <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kamado-joe-konnected-joe-grill-price-specs-133020818.html">Earlier this year</a> , the company combined its add-on controller with its popular charcoal-burning red cookers, resulting in the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Home Depot;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=346ae41c-5265-49ce-a119-79bad16046d5&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Home+Depot&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeSiQg_z4m2agZxV7ktpZJTAt5xo4gemufYTvNQw_Cd9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.homedepot.com%2Fp%2FKamado-Joe-Konnected-Joe-18-in-Digital-Charcoal-Grill-and-Smoker-with-Auto-Ignition-and-Wi-Fi-Temperature-Control-KJ15041123%2F322705036" class="rapid-with-clickid">Konnected Joe</a> .</p><p> At first glance, the Konnected Joe looks like any other ceramic grill in Kamado Joe&#39;s lineup. However, the bottom half is black where most of the company&#39;s other options are solid red. The display (or Kontrol Board) also sets the Konnected Joe apart, and it&#39;s situated beside three food probe jacks, the power button and a temperature dial. Here, you can see temperature graphs, select a cook mode and receive alerts. The grill will also advise you on how to adjust the vents based on your selected temperature. Buttons on the left allow you to set timers and reconnect to WiFi, in addition to adjusting the display to show grill or food temperatures in large numbers visible from afar. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="bc9b73882cda40a9ae82ddcab281fa5a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The Konnected Joe retains a lot of the features that make the company&#39;s ceramic grills great for your deck or patio. The Kontrol Tower top vent, Air Lift hinge and heavy-duty cart all make using the grill easier. Inside, the company&#39;s two-tier Divide &amp; Conquer design allows you to cook different foods at different temperatures by changing the proximity of the stainless steel grates to the fire. You can also set up one side for direct grilling while using a heat deflector for indirect on the other. Most of the components for the grill are semi-circular, which makes the Konnected Joe just as versatile as a regular Kamado Joe. The folding side shelves are modestly sized, but they&#39;re enough to hold a plate, tray or small cutting board.</p><p> Kamado Joe&#39;s latest smart grill is compatible with all of the accessories for the Classic Joe grill, except for the charcoal basket. This means you can add a rotisserie (JoeTisserie), pizza stone (DoJoe) and more to expand the capabilities of the Konnected Joe. There&#39;s a ton of options here, ranging from the affordable half-moon reversible griddle ($70) to the pricey JoeTisserie ($300), with some bundles going for even more. You don&#39;t need to purchase anything extra to get started with the Konnected Joe, though. The grill ships with grates, heat deflectors for low-and-slow cooking and all you need for that optional two-tier configuration. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/5c19c8b3-3555-11ee-b7ff-0d8a68a6ceee" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Kamado Joe 将其智能烧烤专业知识融入到 WiFi 连接模型中，并具有陶瓷炊具的所有优点。 Charcoal offers unique flavor and versatility while the company sells a range of accessories to expand the grill’s toolbox.配套应用程序正在开发中，但它在基础知识方面做得很好。另外，自动点火器将为您省去很多麻烦。" data-uuid="611a730c-9c06-3544-a599-e9dd059320c8"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Just under the three food probe jacks is a dedicated button for the Automatic Fire Starter (AFS). WiFi connectivity may get the bulk of the attention on this Kamado Joe, but the AFS is the real star. It&#39;s essentially a heating element at the bottom of the cooking chamber where you load your charcoal and wood chunks. When you turn it on, it runs for 15 minutes to light your charcoal without any additional lighter fluid or fire starters. I&#39;ve used this every time I&#39;ve cooked with the Konnected Joe, even when I&#39;m otherwise running the grill in Classic Cook Mode without the automatic temperature control. It consistently, completely lit up the charcoal. See ya later, charcoal chimney.</p><p> In addition to built-in WiFi, another key aspect of smart grilling is a mobile app. The Kamado Joe App allows you to adjust time and temperature without being directly in front of the grill. During my tests, changes were typically quick although there have been a few times I had to input the desired temperature twice to get it to stick. Those temperature graphs from the onboard display are here as well, alongside the ability to browse recipes and monitor food probe temps. However, where Kamado Joe currently lags behind the competition is its library of recipes and how they&#39;re presented.</p><p> Right now, there are over 150 recipes available in the Kamado Joe app, organized by food type and cooking method. For comparison, the Traeger app currently houses over 1,000. The Kamado Joe app is also missing a few glaring items, like pulled pork, but the company says it continuously adds new recipes. It also said it&#39;s working to bring recipe videos and step-by-step guidance to the app sometime next year. These are two more items that both Traeger and Weber offer in their apps and they can be a big help when you&#39;re trying a new recipe or are a beginner griller. Still, the app does a solid job with the basics of monitoring and controlling the grill. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/1fa7b4b0-3559-11ee-beff-91f1adb33ddb" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Kamado Joe app" data-uuid="498e1996-78fa-3e2e-927b-eb7c5206eca0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Another area the Kamado Joe app could offer guidance is preparing the grill to cook. There are some tips in recipes, like waiting for clean smoke when you add wood chunks before putting any food on, but there aren&#39;t any tips on how much charcoal to add in the first place. This is a lesson I learned the hard way, as the Konnected Joe would consistently overshoot the set temperature during low-and-slow smoking in my initial tests.</p><p> After consulting with the company, I determined I was using too much charcoal and the extra fuel was igniting before I needed it during the longer sessions. Using less at the start fixed my problem, but extended cooking times may require you to add more. This means moving your food and any racks to the side to access the bottom of the chamber. It&#39;s not ideal, but it&#39;s hardly a dealbreaker.</p><p> None of this means much if the grill can&#39;t produce great-tasting food, and the Konnected Joe does an excellent job in that regard. Since this is mostly a Kamado Joe ceramic grill with some smart-cooking bits added on, its performance is similar to those non-WiFi models. You get the flavor of charcoal, which has a more pronounced smoky essence than pellet grills produce. Sure, you can impart plenty of smoke with wood pellets, but what you get from charcoal is just different. And, at least to me, it&#39;s slightly more intense. You also get the flavor of charcoal through direct cooking for a true grilled essence as opposed to hot-and-fast searing on a pellet grill. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/5c19c8b4-3555-11ee-bdad-2010ef61aeb5" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Kamado Joe 将其智能烧烤专业知识融入到 WiFi 连接模型中，并具有陶瓷炊具的所有优点。 Charcoal offers unique flavor and versatility while the company sells a range of accessories to expand the grill’s toolbox.配套应用程序正在开发中，但它在基础知识方面做得很好。另外，自动点火器将为您省去很多麻烦。" data-uuid="5a69365e-59b2-387b-8247-c90b99b0dc19"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Over the course of testing, I did a mix of high-heat grilling and slow-smoked barbecue. This included a lot of steaks, a Boston Butt for pulled pork, baby back ribs and more. I was consistently impressed by the charcoal smoke flavor present in all of my cooks, especially in the longer sessions for the pork shoulder and ribs. What&#39;s more, the Konnected Joe allows you a bit more room to experiment with types of wood as you add chunks to supplement the charcoal. There are different kinds of pellets intended for different foods, but sometimes those aren&#39;t a single type of wood even if they&#39;re labeled as such. For example, <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Weber USA;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=de57025b-1082-4622-af33-0312dca51a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Weber+USA&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfXrDxRDqLgJABdExZTvE1XdqAlpzjZo0OXfAdVPycOc&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weber.com%2FUS%2Fen%2Faccessories%2Faccessories-by-grill-type%2Fwood-pellet-grill-accessories%2Fcherry-all-natural-hardwood-pellets%25C2%25A0%2F190005.html" class="rapid-with-clickid">Weber&#39;s Cherry pellets</a> are 60 percent Maple. With the Konnected Joe, you can grab a bag of a single type of wood chunks (I use Kingsford) and change them up based on what you&#39;re cooking.</p><p> Another thing you need to be aware of (and this applies to ceramic grills in general) is the long cool-down period. Due to the nature of the materials, these models retain heat a lot more efficiently than a kettle or gas grill – or even most pellet options. This is great while you&#39;re cooking, but it also means you need to plan for an extended time for the grill to cool off before you can put the cover on. As an example, I finished cooking ribs around 5PM at a temperature of 275 degrees (a five-hour cook). When I locked up for the night around 11PM, the grill was still warm to the touch, so I couldn&#39;t cover it yet. High-heat searing required even more time to cool off, and in most cases, I had to leave the grill uncovered until the next day. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/5c19c8b1-3555-11ee-9e5d-e144b0ae5c53" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Kamado Joe 将其智能烧烤专业知识融入到 WiFi 连接模型中，并具有陶瓷炊具的所有优点。 Charcoal offers unique flavor and versatility while the company sells a range of accessories to expand the grill’s toolbox.配套应用程序正在开发中，但它在基础知识方面做得很好。另外，自动点火器将为您省去很多麻烦。" data-uuid="2d96fd22-700e-3ff7-b7f9-c50734f655c5"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> One area where the Konnected Joe surpasses WiFi-enabled pellet grills is the ease of cleanup. You only need to use the included ash tool to scrape debris through the holes in the bottom of the cooking chamber, leaving larger pieces of used charcoal for the next cook. A tray inside the bottom vent slides out for easy disposal. If there&#39;s a large amount of ash, you may need to use the tool to scrape that slot, but you shouldn&#39;t need to get out the shop vac like you do for a pellet grill. Of course, the accessories may require a thorough scrubbing after use, but that&#39;s nothing some grill cleaner or soapy water can&#39;t handle.</p><p> If you&#39;re looking for a charcoal-burning alternative to the Konnected Joe, you don&#39;t have to go far. Parent company Middleby Outdoor also owns the Masterbuilt brand that has the Gravity Series smart grills <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/masterbuilt-gravity-series-560-review-smart-charcoal-grill-160050858.html">we tested in 2020</a> . While the Gravity Series 560 was the first version, the company has since introduced the larger <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/masterbuilt-gravity-series-800-grill-smoker-wifi-griddle-140047644.html">Gravity Series 800</a> that comes with a griddle insert and the <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.masterbuilt.com/products/gravity-series-1050-digital-charcoal-grill-smoker">Gravity Series 1050</a> with the largest cooking capacity of the trio.</p><p> The design is the same across all three models: a gravity-fed hopper on the right side funnels charcoal down to a digitally-controlled fan to maintain temperatures. You can add wood chunks to the ash bin to produce more smoke. The Gravity Series is capable of hot-and-fast searing, low-and-slow smoking and everything in between, all with the ability to monitor temperatures from your sofa. One key issue with those grills is they can be difficult to light when you have used charcoal at the bottom of the hopper, so it&#39;s best to cycle through and have fresh fuel to light, mixing any used bits mid-chamber. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/5c170990-3555-11ee-b67d-f666155a79c0" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Kamado Joe 将其智能烧烤专业知识融入到 WiFi 连接模型中，并具有陶瓷炊具的所有优点。 Charcoal offers unique flavor and versatility while the company sells a range of accessories to expand the grill’s toolbox.配套应用程序正在开发中，但它在基础知识方面做得很好。另外，自动点火器将为您省去很多麻烦。" data-uuid="5eda2fe5-b190-3cb7-a78e-268ed4278117"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> If ease of use is your top priority, a pellet model is worth considering <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-grills-and-how-to-choose-one-153006286.html">when shopping for a smart grill</a> . In addition to full-featured apps for monitoring and controlling the grill from afar, Traeger and Weber both offer easy-to-follow recipe guidance. Both companies also give you estimated completion times in their apps ( <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/traeger-grills-wireless-meat-thermometer-meater-acquisition-183944452.html">via Meater for Traeger</a> ) so you have an idea of when to have the sides ready (and to keep hungry guests informed of the situation).</p><p> What&#39;s more, pellet grills don&#39;t require you to futz with components to add more fuel as you simply refill the hopper outside of the cooking area if you start to run low. Cleanup is a little more involved, but for longer cooks that don&#39;t require any spritzing to keep the meat moist or wrapping to expedite cooking, this type of grill is truly set it and forget it. Weber&#39;s most recent model is the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/weber-smokefire-sear-plus-announced-140007112.html">SmokeFire Sear+</a> , which offers over 1,000 square inches of cooking space <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Weber USA;elmt:;cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=de57025b-1082-4622-af33-0312dca51a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Weber+USA&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQHtAhEG-9rZeooScJ6-KdkG2L8OD8okpKi1-euPAXZD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weber.com%2FUS%2Fen%2Fwood-pellet%2Fsmokefire-sear%252B-elx6%2F23722001.html" class="rapid-with-clickid">for $1,599</a> . The best new Traeger for most people is the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/traegers-redesigned-ironwood-grills-pack-touchscreen-controls-and-more-efficiency-150010372.html">recently redesigned Ironwood</a> , <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy50cmFlZ2VyLmNvbS9wZWxsZXQtZ3JpbGxzL2lyb253b29kIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4ZTM3ZDJjYy1iNWYyLTQ4MGYtYjIwNC0zMjgyYmVjYmU4NGEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAARnWKNNRfc1tpSvQc07C7FEeFnQdWLF0nLm4sUxTyYdi&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.traeger.com%2Fpellet-grills%2Fironwood" class="rapid-with-clickid">the smaller version of which is $1,800</a> .</p><p> At <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Home Depot;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=346ae41c-5265-49ce-a119-79bad16046d5&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Home+Depot&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeSiQg_z4m2agZxV7ktpZJTAt5xo4gemufYTvNQw_Cd9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.homedepot.com%2Fp%2FKamado-Joe-Konnected-Joe-18-in-Digital-Charcoal-Grill-and-Smoker-with-Auto-Ignition-and-Wi-Fi-Temperature-Control-KJ15041123%2F322705036" class="rapid-with-clickid">$1,699</a> , the Konnected Joe is very expensive for a charcoal grill. However, it&#39;s more affordable than the <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.kamadojoe.com/products/classic-joe-iii">Classic Joe Series III</a> , which offers the same cooking area without the connectivity and AFS igniter. A comparably sized Big Green Egg is around $1,100, but again, you&#39;ll need a secondary device for any kind of temperature monitoring. When you pit it against WiFi-equipped pellet grills, the Konnected Joe isn&#39;t that far off. In fact, it&#39;s slightly cheaper than Kamado Joe&#39;s own <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kamado-joe-pellet-joe-ceramic-smart-grill-specs-price-availability-201946770.html">Pellet Joe</a> . A connected grill and all the convenience that it affords has never been cheap, but the Konnected Joe pairs all the versatility of a ceramic cooker with the advantages of charcoal and performs well. If the company can expand and refine its companion app, this grill will be a complete package – even if it commands a steep investment.</p><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="c7cd95b6-32d3-43d5-9d3c-d323e7935f9c" /><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/kamado-joe-konnected-joe-review-a-highly-versatile-smart-grill-140043770.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/kamado-joe-konnected-joe-review-a-highly-versatile-smart-grill-140043770.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8e37d2cc-b5f2-480f-b204-3282becbe84a</guid><dc:creator> Billy Steele</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 14:00:43 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691501333</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T13:29:19+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Billy Steele]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/5c19c8b0-3555-11ee-9afe-c37a0fba3ca9" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/5c19c8b0-3555-11ee-9afe-c37a0fba3ca9" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Kamado Joe put its smart-grilling expertise into a WiFi-connected model with all the benefits of a ceramic cooker. Charcoal offers unique flavor and versatility while the company sells a range of accessories to expand the grill’s toolbox. The companion app is a work in progress, but it does well with the basics. Plus, that Automatic Fire Starter will save you lots of headaches.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Kamado Joe Konnected Joe review]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Marvel's visual effects workers vote to unionize]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Marvel&#39;s visual effects employees have voted in favor of joining a union in their fight for better pay, overtime compensation, more benefits and better treatment. According to <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.vulture.com/2023/08/vfx-workers-vote-to-unionize-at-marvel-for-the-first-time.html"><em>Vulture</em></a> , a supermajority of the company&#39;s 50 on-set VFX employees have filed a petition for an election with the National Labor Relations Board. They&#39;re hoping to join the Theatrical Stage Employees (IATSE), which also represents hair and makeup artists, wardrobe, lighting and prop personnel, among other workers. Because apparently, despite Marvel&#39;s reliance on visual effects to make its universe(s), superheroes and supervillains look real on the big screen, its VFX artists aren&#39;t represented by a union. IATSE has also been <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://iatse.net/growing-our-union-further/">campaigning</a> broadly to expand its membership into VFX and animation workers in recent months.</p><p> Several current and former VFX employees for the company previously spoke out about grueling schedules and breaking down under pressure while working on shows and movies for the studio. Sources told <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://sea.ign.com/she-hulk-2/189387/news/pressure-crunch-blacklist-fears-the-mcus-visual-effects-artists-speak-out"><em>IGN</em></a> that people were being given tasks that were impossible to finish within the timeframe allowed to complete them. Some VFX artists told <em>Vulture</em> that the hectic production schedule for <em>Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania</em> , for instance, <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ant-man-and-the-wasp-quantumania-review-bad-vfx-130036373.html">led to rushed work</a> and an end product that many reviewers had described as &quot;bland.&quot;</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> VFX coordinator Bella Huffman said: &quot;Turnaround times don&#39;t apply to us, protected hours don&#39;t apply to us, and pay equity doesn&#39;t apply to us. Visual effects must become a sustainable and safe department for everyone who&#39;s suffered far too long and for all newcomers who need to know they won&#39;t be exploited.&quot;</p><p> <em>Vulture</em> says a strike by Marvel&#39;s VFX artists is not out of the question. It is a common tactic employed by workers seeking to organize, after all — plus, both the <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hollywood-writers-are-officially-on-strike-084059607.html">Writers Guild</a> and the <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/striking-actors-say-rejected-ai-proposal-would-let-studios-use-their-likeness-without-fair-pay-000025878.html">Screen Actors Guild</a> are currently on strike to demand better pay, streaming residuals from successful shows and regulation of AI use in Hollywood.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/marvels-visual-effects-workers-vote-to-join-a-union-123036176.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/marvels-visual-effects-workers-vote-to-join-a-union-123036176.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a2ce83d4-15d0-46c9-bad8-78fba27b059e</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:30:36 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691501776</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T13:36:23+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Labor Issues]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="3069" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/0dd64770-35df-11ee-b3bd-f6ff85700840" width="4603"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3069" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/0dd64770-35df-11ee-b3bd-f6ff85700840" width="4603"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A popcorn and Marvel logo displayed on a screen in the background are seen in this illustration photo taken in Krakow, Poland on August 7, 2023. (Photo by Jakub Porzycki/NurPhoto via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Movie Industry Photo Illustrations]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best PS5 games for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Welcome to Engadget&#39;s best PS5 games list. As always, we have looked for games that generally offer meaningful improvements over their last-gen counterparts when played on PS5, or are exclusive to the system. We&#39;ll be updating this periodically, so, if a game&#39;s just been released and you don&#39;t see it, chances are that the reason for its absence is that we haven&#39;t played through it yet. Either that or we hate it.</p><h2> Stray </h2><p><core-commerce id="7e266bc2eb204ae4b1f470a053abfcf6" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <em>Stray</em> a perfectly contained adventure game that has you embodying a cat in a post-apocalyptic world humans have left behind. It has plenty of fresh ideas, each one pared down to its purest form. Plenty of actions in <em>Stray</em> exist simply because they make sense for a cat protagonist (and probably because they&#39;re cute as hell). There&#39;s a discrete button to meow, and the robots the cat shares its world with react with shock and frustration when you cut across their board game, throwing pieces to the floor. It&#39;s possible to curl up and sleep basically any time, anywhere – even directly on top of a robot stranger. When the cat gets pets and cuddles from the robots, it purrs and the DualSense&#39;s haptics fire up in response. The environmental puzzles take advantage of this cat-level perspective, inviting players to look at the world with different, light-reflective eyes.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> As well as puzzle-solving, ledge-leaping and blob-dodging, <em>Stray</em> introduces a world of lighthearted dystopia, where robots don&#39;t hate the humans that came before them. Instead, they attempt to cultivate plants that can survive in the dark, just because people would have liked that. Compared with most dystopian cyberpunk games, <em>Stray</em> is downright joyful.</p><h2> Dead Space </h2><p><core-commerce id="918b9b78825b40e1bcb35bfcf6a74dee" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>这<em>&nbsp;</em> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9EZWFkLVNwYWNlLVBsYXlTdGF0aW9uLTUvZHAvQjBCUlA4WVlGNC8_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tZHgtMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjQ1MmQ2NzI5LWYxMzYtNDc1Yy05YmM1LTU4ZjhlMGViY2M2NCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAerWwB99hdMp6SS7bxHlZf5X5Xn9MTyWugOsMzIyCbbv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDead-Space-PlayStation-5%2Fdp%2FB0BRP8YYF4%2F" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Dead-Space-PlayStation-5/dp/B0BRP8YYF4/?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>Dead Space</em></a> remake feels like a warm, juicy hug from a murderous necromorph, and we mean that in the best way possible. The <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dead-space-remake-playstation-5-review-160019905.html">2023 version</a> of <em>Dead Space</em> spit-shines the mechanics that made the original game so magically horrific back in 2008, and it doesn&#39;t add any unnecessary, modern bloat. The remake features full voice acting, new puzzles and expanded storylines, and it introduces a zero-gravity ability that allows the protagonist, Isaac Clarke, to fly through sections of the game in an ultra-satisfying way.</p><p> None of these additions outshine the game&#39;s core loop: <em>stasis, shoot, stomp</em> . Isaac gains the ability to temporarily freeze enemies and he picks up a variety of weapons, but he never feels overpowered; he&#39;s always in danger. Mutilated corpse monsters appear suddenly in the cramped corridors of the space station, charging at Isaac from the shadows, limbs akimbo and begging to be shot off. The first <em>Dead Space</em> popularized the idea that headshots don&#39;t matter and the remake stays true to this ethos – yet its combat rhythm still feels fresh.</p><p> The 2023 version of <em>Dead Space</em> proves that innovative game design is timeless (and so are plasma cutters).</p><h2> <strong>Gran Turismo 7</strong> </h2><p><core-commerce id="055bb59a3d9744b2ac3d1a4fb9baa48b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you enjoy sim-style racing games, <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAU11iNqSnv8jl-hqI5s9GXD6G4TlpHq6Ni8cmWKuT1_y&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGran-Turismo-7-Standard-PlayStation-5%2Fdp%2FB09SW6GCGL%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>Gran Turismo 7</em></a> is the PS5&#39;s only real choice. The main tenets that&#39;ve made <em>Gran Turismo</em> a gaming staple are still here: a handling and physics model that demands precision but isn&#39;t so realistic that you need a wheel or intense skill to play; the intensity of learning how a specific car meshes with a specific track; truly stunning visuals; that odd mix of rock, jazz and orchestral music in the soundtrack. Most of all, there remains a deep love of the automobile, from sexy speed demons to unwieldy boxes from years ago. More than this, <em>Gran Turismo 7</em> is <em>romantic</em> about cars, not just for how they look, but how they represent years of collective labor and passion. There&#39;s a singular style and voice here that just doesn&#39;t exist in most sports games.</p><p> There was lots of anger around <em>Gran Turismo 7</em> ’s microtransactions, amount of content and event payouts around launch – just look at that <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-5/gran-turismo-7">Metacritic user score</a> – and the fact that it&#39;s effectively always-online is still a major detraction. But if you&#39;re starting today, you&#39;ll have hundreds of hours of things to do, and you shouldn&#39;t feel the need to grind for credits until far down the road. And that&#39;s assuming you aren&#39;t interested in racing against other players online, which is where the game should be most lively for years to come.</p><h2> Elden Ring </h2><p><core-commerce id="277bdb8bf2694cd9be8c2862e6ba5755" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Did you think this list would not include <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQbWiQz7OlFyfay67eLN9ZhbHhcR1M0QjvW6eOMbURUl&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FElden-Ring-PlayStation-5%2Fdp%2FB09743F8P6%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Elden-Ring-PlayStation-5/dp/B09743F8P6/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2YGAF3ZH2WWVJ&amp;keywords=elden+ring&amp;qid=1687795177&amp;sprefix=elden+rin%2Caps%2C103&amp;sr=8-1" class="rapid-with-clickid"><em>Elden Ring</em></a> ? The strengths of FromSoftware&#39;s latest action-RPG are many, but what&#39;s most impressive about the game is how hand-crafted it feels despite its scale. <em>Elden Ring</em> is big, but it never feels like it&#39;s wasting your time. Far from it; FromSoftware has created a rich open world, with something surprising, delightful or utterly terrifying around every corner. I&#39;ll never forget the moment I found a chest that teleported my character to a cave full of Eldritch monsters. <em>Elden Ring</em> is full of those kinds of discoveries.</p><p> And if you&#39;re worried about hitting a brick wall with <em>Elden Ring’s</em> difficulty, don&#39;t be. Sure, it can be tough as nails, but it&#39;s also From&#39;s most accessible game to date as well. If you find combat overly punishing, go for a mage build and blast your enemies from afar. And if all else fails, one of the rewards for exploring <em>Elden Ring&#39;s</em> world is experience that you can use to make your character stronger.</p><h2> God of War: Ragnarök </h2><p><core-commerce id="fa7bd1d6917a49ebbfaa1d4de69ad83a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> 2018&#39;s <em>God of War</em> was a brilliant reinvention for a franchise that was in desperate need of a reboot. For an encore, all Sony&#39;s Santa Monica Studio did was every single stake they could. <em>God of War Ragnarök</em> is a massive adventure, taking protagonist Kratos and his son Atreus all over the nine Norse realms as they prepare for Ragnarök, a mythical event essentially meant to bring about the end of the world. Along the way, Kratos and Atreus get up close and personal with even more of the Norse gods, including stunning encounters with the drunken but deadly Thor and, of course, Odin himself.</p><p> The combat in <em>Ragnarök</em> remains one of the most satisfying gaming experiences I can think of – it&#39;s fluid and extremely customizable. And once you get into a groove and power up Kratos, it&#39;s truly a god-like experience. There&#39;s also a much greater variety of enemies this time out, from the smaller grunts you mow through to bigger and more intense boss battles. There are more realms to visit, more sidequests than ever and an endgame sequence that&#39;s up there with the biggest battles any God of War game has ever put to screen. The backdrop for all this is some of the most beautifully detailed and varied environments you can find, from the swampy confines of Vanaheim and the fiery to the frozen tundra of Midgard. On the PS5, you can choose between native 4K visuals or high frame rates up to 120Hz, provided your TV can handle it.</p><h2> The Last of Us </h2><p><core-commerce id="14a18bf81d694cd9965689e14fb52e8c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <em>The Last of Us</em> and its sequel may have originally come out for the PS3 and PS4, respectively, but they also provide two excellent PS5 experiences. <em>The Last of Us Part I</em> is a complete visual remake for the PS5 of the 2013 original, with massively improved character models and environments, along with native 4K visuals or frame rates up to 120 fps. <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYeyu0p_pWAyd4mjRvmr54p4LzrpcsVkQLHQwtS4Ftws&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLast-Us-Part-II-PlayStation-4%2Fdp%2FB07DJRFSDF"><em>The Last of Us Part II</em></a> originally launched for the PS4 in 2020, and developer Naughty Dog released a patch for it last year unlocking 60 fps gameplay on the PS5. There weren&#39;t any other major updates, but the game already looked amazing on the PS4 so there wasn&#39;t a ton to change here. Either way, the PS5 is the best place to experience these two games.</p><p> Both games feature a sprawling post-pandemic adventure story, following survivors Joel and Ellie through a gorgeously rendered but terrifying world where zombie-like Infected and regular humans alike are out for your blood. You&#39;ll never really feel like you have enough supplies to survive, so you need to make every shot count – or figure out how to sneak around enemies or craft tools that&#39;ll get you out of tight spots. There&#39;s an ever-present sense of danger in these games, while the stories focus on human connection in all its messy glory; the tone is often extremely grim, but there are moments of levity, humor and hope sprinkled throughout the ruined world. <em>The Last of Us Part I</em> and <em>Part II</em> both put you through an intense, violent and emotional experience, but they remain a journey worth taking.</p><h2> Rollerdrome </h2><p><core-commerce id="6a246c22f4214d91b52a38e510a31774" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <em>Rollerdrome</em> is lush. It&#39;s incredibly stylish, taking cues from 1970s Hollywood sci-fi but with an attractive cel-shaded filter over every scene. Even better than its stunning visuals, <em>Rollerdrome</em> has smooth, precise mechanics that allow players to fall into a flow in every level. The game is all about gliding through the environments on rollerblades, picking up speed and doing tricks while dodging and shooting enemies, managing weapons and controlling time – and it all comes together in a thrilling dystopian bloodsport.</p><p> It&#39;s a joy to dodge, dodge, dodge and then leap into the air, slow down time and take out the people shooting at you, refilling ammo and collecting health in the process. Meanwhile, an unsettling story of corporate greed unfolds naturally beneath the rollerblading bloodshed, keeping the stakes high. <em>Rollerdrome</em> was a sleeper hit of 2022, so if you&#39;ve been napping on this one, now&#39;s the time to wake up and play.</p><h2> Overwatch 2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="8c36cc8de6444c948b12a9c0a9911d32" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Even though Blizzard has improved the onramp for new players this time around, <em>Overwatch 2</em> still has a steep learning curve. Stick with it, though, and you&#39;ll get to indulge in perhaps the best team shooter around. <em>Overwatch 2</em> has a deceptively simple goal — stand on or near an objective and keep the other team away long enough to win. It&#39;s much more complex in practice. To the untrained eye, matches may seem like colorful chaos, but <em>Overwatch 2</em> has a deceptively simple goal — stand on or near an objective and keep the other team away long enough to win.</p><p> It&#39;s much more complex in practice. Blizzard reduced the number of players on each team from six to five. That, along with across-the-board character tweaks, has made gameplay faster-paced and more enjoyable compared with the original <em>Overwatch</em> . There&#39;s a greater emphasis on individual impact, but you&#39;ll still need to work well with your teammates to secure a victory.</p><p> Now featuring a cast of more than 30 heroes, each with distinct abilities and playstyles, you&#39;ll surely find a few <em>Overwatch 2</em> characters that you can connect with. The first batch of new heroes are all a blast to play. There are many great (though often fairly expensive) new skins to kit them out with too. The game looks and sounds terrific too, thanks to Blizzard&#39;s trademark level of polish. At least until you figure out how to play <em>Overwatch 2</em> , you can marvel at how good it looks.</p><h2> Astro&#39;s Playroom </h2><p><core-commerce id="3bc97e6027b3442eb9f90ff0aa599c53" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> It&#39;s odd to start a best games list with a title that comes free with the console, but if you&#39;re anything like my son, who swiftly deleted <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5wbGF5c3RhdGlvbi5jb20vZW4tdXMvZ2FtZXMvYXN0cm9zLXBsYXlyb29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNDUyZDY3MjktZjEzNi00NzVjLTliYzUtNThmOGUwZWJjYzY0In0&amp;signature=AQAAARyhZ2-STAUhBsc4fQ5UbMgeniWiOVLoWpihjV5FSKpr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fgames%2Fastros-playroom%2F"><em>Astro&#39;s Playroom</em></a> to make space for various Call of Duty titles, I&#39;m here to tell you to give the pack-in title another shot. <em>Astro&#39;s Playroom</em> is a love letter to both 3D platformers and the PlayStation itself. It&#39;s also, to date, the title that makes the best use of Sony&#39;s DualSense controller, with incredible haptic feedback and clever usage of the pad&#39;s adaptive triggers. (Although, eight years on, I&#39;m still not convinced anyone has found a compelling reason for that touch pad.) It&#39;s a game that even completionists can finish within six hours or so, but those six hours were among the most fun I&#39;ve had with the PS5 so far.</p><h2> <strong>Final Fantasy VII Remake: Intergrade</strong> </h2><p><core-commerce id="e404a41152e5460e835241b2e1e58b13" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> We thought it would never happen. <em>Final Fantasy VII</em> was an iconic JRPG that&#39;s credited with opening up the genre to the west. It peppered the Top 10 lists of the best games of all-time and introduced the long-running Japanese RPG series to polygons, 3D maps, and countless other innovations of 32-bit consoles. 23 years later, and three PlayStation iterations later, Square Enix dared to remake, not remaster, the game. It would be, contentiously, episodic, expanding out the story of Midgar and the opening part of the game into a single game.</p><p> It&#39;s all very different. It&#39;s also gorgeous, with a modern battle system that no longer focuses on static characters and menu choices. Somehow, and we were ready to be underwhelmed, the battle system works. <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:GameStop;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ffe106af-8248-4af3-9098-a2d4fd637766&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=GameStop&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAafv3Epls3ZHNu7i50nd9W8E6u-MoLqkBxudJ5uF16H3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fvideo-games%2Fplaystation-5%2Fproducts%2Ffinal-fantasy-vii-remake-intergrade---playstation-5%2F296955.html%3F"><em>FF7R’s</em></a> fights are slicker and more enjoyable than those in Final Fantasy XV, the latest entry in the series. Each character, from iconic mercenary Cloud through to eco-terrorist Barret and flower girl Aerith, play in entirely different ways, using the space between themselves and enemies in very different ways. Some sub-missions and distractions feel like they&#39;re there solely to eke some more hours out of your playthrough, but the world of the original has been thoughtfully reimagined, so it&#39;s a minor complaint.</p><p> For anyone that bought the PS4 iteration, the upgrade to PS5 is free. However, it costs money to gain access to the PS5-exclusive DLC chapter featuring ninja Yuffie. Offering another battle style to experiment with and master, two new extra chapters run alongside the events of the first installment of this remake. Moments of the game feel like they were built to tease how capable the newest PlayStation is, with Yuffie zipping down poles through vertiginous levels, wall-running and mixing up long-range and short-range attacks in a completely different way to Cloud, Aerith and the rest. It suffers a little from trying to tie in <em>FF7</em> lore from old spin-off titles, but it&#39;s a satisfying distraction as we wait for the second part – <em>Final Fantasy VII Rebirth</em> – to arrive in 2023.</p><h2> Demon&#39;s Souls </h2><p><core-commerce id="03b3c750848f4cb6879c661c0449856d" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Bluepoint&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUF0PsZEHi2Zg-LFgwFicrQJiToXGJ6Ch6zVDmU354H3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDemons-Souls-PlayStation-5%2Fdp%2FB08FC5TTBF"><em>Demon&#39;s Souls</em></a> remake won&#39;t be for everyone — no Souls game is. The original <em>Demon&#39;s Souls</em> was a sleeper hit in 2009 on the PS3, establishing the basic formula that would later be cemented with <em>Dark Souls</em> , and then aped by an entire industry to the point where we now essentially have a “Soulslike&#39;&#39; genre. Today, that means challenging difficulty, grinding enemies for souls to level up, the retrieval of your corpse to collect said souls, a labyrinthine map to explore and, if you&#39;re doing Soulslike right, some show-stopping boss fights to contend with. As a progenitor to the genre, <em>Demon&#39;s Souls</em> has most of those in abundance. But rather than a huge sprawling map, it uses a portal system, with mini labyrinths to work through. Its bosses are also not quite on the level of impressiveness or difficulty of a more modern Dark Souls game.</p><p> Bluepoint has been faithful to the original, then, but graphically <em>Demon&#39;s Souls</em> is a true showcase of what the PS5 can do, with gorgeous high-resolution visuals, smooth frame rates and swift loading. While the graphics certainly catch your eye, it&#39;s the smoothness and loading times that are the most impactful. The original ran at 720p, and… depending on what you were doing 25 to 30 fps, while the remake lets you pick between a locked 30 or 60 fps at 4K or 1440p. And in a game that will likely kill you hundreds of times, waiting two seconds to respawn instead of thirty is transformative.</p><h2> God of War </h2><p><core-commerce id="3268a861dc2343a19409bd8b7999d4df" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Sony&#39;s God of War series had laid dormant for half a decade when its latest incarnation hit stores in early 2018, and for good reason. Antiquated gameplay and troubling themes had made it an ill-fit for the modern gaming landscape.不再。 SIE Santa Monica Studio&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:GameStop;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ffe106af-8248-4af3-9098-a2d4fd637766&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=GameStop&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASwD9StCBfDFThDbPQpbMxKSp5N6gyzIEbGG3uzxHnzI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fvideo-games%2Fproducts%2Fgod-of-war---playstation-4%2F127507.html"><em>God of War</em></a> manages to successfully reboot the series while turning the previous games&#39; narrative weaknesses into its strengths. Kratos is now a dad, the camera is now essentially strapped to his shoulder and Sony has what is sure to become a new series on its hands.</p><p> The first outright PS4 game on this collection, <em>God of War</em> has at least been patched for better performance on PS5, allowing it to output at 4K/60. For those subscribed to PS Plus, this one&#39;s available for free as part of the <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5wbGF5c3RhdGlvbi5jb20vZW4tdXMvcHMtcGx1cy8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjQ1MmQ2NzI5LWYxMzYtNDc1Yy05YmM1LTU4ZjhlMGViY2M2NCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAYGp-SQg1xwma8AZY5BajQ6fC0TUQg01gDQoGJYjkmRo&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fps-plus%2F">PlayStation Plus Collection</a> on PS5.</p><h2> Ghost of Tsushima: The Director&#39;s Cut </h2><p><core-commerce id="aa628a8e55434426b83db492c98c3c40" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> This tale of samurai vengeance is like Japanese cinema come to life. There are multiple betrayals, the sad deaths of several close allies, tense sword fights, villages and castles under siege, and even a &#39;Kurosawa mode&#39; black-and-white filter you employ for the entire game. The world of feudal Japan, with some creative liberties, is gorgeous, with fields of grass and bullrushes to race through on your faithful steed, temple &#39;puzzles&#39; to navigate around and fortresses to assess and attack.</p><p> As you make your way through the main story quest, and more than enough side quests and challenges, you unlock more powerful sword techniques and stances, as well as new weapons and forbidden techniques that are neatly woven in the story of a samurai pushed to the edge. It still suffers from one too many fetch quests, artifacts scattered across Japan&#39;s prefectures, but the sheer beauty of <em>Ghost of Tsushima</em> tricks you into believing this is the greatest open-world game on PlayStation. Don&#39;t get me wrong — it&#39;s up there.</p><p> With the new <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARgfrm2sRkVOyaOOpEDs4J94q79CF_7IfAGfd7-N9qo1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGhost-Tsushima-Directors-Cut-PS5%2Fdp%2FB098TV5XPX%3F"><em>Director&#39;s Cut</em></a> edition on the PS5, you also get dynamic frame-rates up to 60 FPS, ensuring the game looks and feels even more like a tribute to Japanese cinematic auteurs of the past. There are also DualSense tricks, like a bow that tangibly tightens as you pull on trigger buttons, and subtle rumble as you ride across the lands of Tsushima, <em>Director&#39;s Cut</em> adds a new, surprisingly compelling DLC chapter. As you explore the Iki isle, the game adds a few more tricks to Jin&#39;s arsenal, and deepens the relationship and history between the game&#39;s hero and his father.</p><p> Without spoiling what happens, the game smartly threads the original story into the DLC, ensuring it feels solidly connected to the main game, despite DLC status.</p><h2> Deathloop </h2><p><core-commerce id="59557435bcd84c20b4231f70ad451d90" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:GameStop;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ffe106af-8248-4af3-9098-a2d4fd637766&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=GameStop&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmZmUxMDZhZi04MjQ4LTRhZjMtOTA5OC1hMmQ0ZmQ2Mzc3NjYiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ2FtZXN0b3AuY29tL3ZpZGVvLWdhbWVzL3Byb2R1Y3RzL2RlYXRobG9vcC0tLXBsYXlzdGF0aW9uLTUvMjMyODUwLmh0bWw_IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI0NTJkNjcyOS1mMTM2LTQ3NWMtOWJjNS01OGY4ZTBlYmNjNjQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAWAEepFdrgDmk9qK3G2VKJY-JF2vj9AMhIWZwXeKGDX5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fvideo-games%2Fproducts%2Fdeathloop---playstation-5%2F232850.html%3F"><em>Deathloop</em></a> , from the studio that brought you the Dishonored series, is easy enough to explain: You&#39;re trapped in a day that repeats itself. If you die, then you go back to the morning, to repeat the day again. If you last until the end of the day, you still repeat it again. Colt must “break the loop” by efficiently murdering seven main characters, who are inconveniently are never in the same place at the same time. It&#39;s also stylish, accessible and fun.</p><p> While you try to figure out your escape from this time anomaly, you&#39;ll also be hunted down by Julianna, another island resident who, like you, is able to remember everything that happens in each loop. She&#39;ll also lock you out of escaping an area, and generally interfere with your plans to escape the time loop. (The online multiplayer is also addictive, flipping the roles around. You play as Julianna, hunting down Colt and foiling his plans for murder. )</p><p> As you play through the areas again (and again) you&#39;ll equip yourself with slabs that add supernatural powers, as well as more potent weapons and trinkets to embed into both guns and yourself. It&#39;s through this that you&#39;re able to customize your playstyle or equip yourself in the best way to survive Julianna and nail that assassination. Each time period and area rewards repeat exploration, with secret guns, hidden conversations with NPCs and lots of world-building lore to discover for yourself.</p><h2> Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man Ultimate Edition </h2><p><core-commerce id="838613749ce54b6482da9c03e9a36138" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Finally, you don&#39;t have to pick up <em>Spider-Man 2</em> on the GameCube to get your web-slinging fix anymore. For almost 15 years, that game was held as the gold standard for a Spider-Man game, and I&#39;ll let you into a secret: It wasn&#39;t actually that good. <em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man</em> , on the other hand, is a tour de force. Featuring the best representation of what it&#39;s like to swing through New York City, well, ever, Insomniac&#39;s PlayStation exclusive also borrows liberally from the Batman: Arkham series&#39; combat and throws in a story that, although it takes a while to get going, ends up in a jaw-dropping place.</p><p> With the launch of the PS5, Insomniac released a <em>Miles Morales</em> spin-off game, which follows the eponymous character as he attempts to protect NYC in Peter Parker&#39;s absence. Both parts are available packaged together as <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:GameStop;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ffe106af-8248-4af3-9098-a2d4fd637766&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=GameStop&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZZA74XiVAN7YoRsaRnrFR--B5EvrDn0jHlTByU91NQY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fvideo-games%2Fproducts%2Fmarvels-spider-man-miles-morales-ultimate-edition---playstation-5%2F225341.html%3F"><em>Spider-Man Ultimate Edition</em></a> — it has a longer name than that but let&#39;s not — and benefit from improved framerates, resolution and ray tracing (although not necessarily all at the same time!) With the full graphical package enabled, you&#39;ll be playing at 30 frames per second in 4K, or you can pick between a pair of performance options: 4K/60 with no ray tracing, or 1080p/60 with ray-tracing. Whatever mode you pick, you&#39;ll benefit from loading times that finally make the game&#39;s fast travel system… fast.</p><h2> Resident Evil Village </h2><p><core-commerce id="db89b59178e64c678683a1a427a616a2" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQz8NecIvyAf97jSKuf5lrxEomIxgG0K7P9VWXZSN8vw&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FResident-Evil-Village-PlayStation-5-Standard%2Fdp%2FB08TYCWK3C"><em>Resident Evil Village</em></a> is delightful. It&#39;s a gothic fairy tale masquerading as a survival-horror game, and while this represents a fresh vibe for the franchise, it&#39;s not an unwelcome evolution. The characters and enemies in Village are full of life — even when they&#39;re decidedly undead — and Capcom has put a delicious twist on the idea of vampires, werewolves, sea creatures, giants and creepy dolls. The game retains its horror, puzzle and action roots, and it has Umbrella Corporation&#39;s fingerprints all over it. On PS5, the game is gorgeous and it plays nicely with the DualSense controller, adding haptic feedback to weapons and terrifying situations alike. It simply feels like developers had fun with this one, and so will you.</p><h2> Returnal </h2><p><core-commerce id="3ab7a8c85942414a8a7ee892f9463abe" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:GameStop;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ffe106af-8248-4af3-9098-a2d4fd637766&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=GameStop&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWI7_GcIaDdBnnDldmNe2DdpbqbQGbJSWgylHqHYXAW7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fvideo-games%2Fplaystation-5%2Fproducts%2Freturnal---playstation-5%2F234470.html%3F"><em>Returnal</em></a> <em>&nbsp;</em> is a third-person action game, a roguelite, a bullet-hell shooter and very hard, perhaps not in that order. The setup is basically that you&#39;re stuck in a death loop, but you&#39;re aware of it, and must learn the patterns and weaknesses of enemies — and master your own — in order to progress. <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/returnal-review-ps5-shooter-133029657.html">As <em>Devindra Hardwar</em> explains</a> , it leans heavily on the dark sci-fi of <em>Alien</em> , <em>Edge of Tomorrow</em> and <em>Event Horizon</em> but makes something new and unique in the process.</p><p> It&#39;s made by the team behind <em>Resogun</em> , <em>Nex Machina</em> and <em>Super Stardust HD</em> , and you can tell, for better or worse. As you&#39;d expect from a team that&#39;s spent the past decades making shooters, the movement, gunplay and enemy attack patterns are incredibly well tuned. But on the flipside, from a studio used to smaller productions, the complexity and ambition of <em>Returnal</em> leads to a lack of polish that some may find unacceptable in a $70 game. If you can look past that, there&#39;s a hell of a game waiting for you here.</p><h2> Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice </h2><p><core-commerce id="9bc08cd49f354ab0bf2d9fb899f4ab91" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAc4Vutg-7Mctuq7keOO2Sls8TJLTnhYALM99CdquyMiL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSekiro-Shadows-Die-Twice-PlayStation-4%2Fdp%2FB07DJWBYJN"><em>Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice</em></a> isn&#39;t just another Dark Souls game. FromSoftware&#39;s samurai adventure is a departure from that well-established formula, replacing slow, weighty combat and gothic despair for stealth, grappling hooks and swift swordplay. Oh, and while it&#39;s still a difficult game, it&#39;s a lot more accessible than Souls games — you can even pause it! The result of all these changes is something that&#39;s still instantly recognizable as a FromSoftware title, but it&#39;s its own thing, and it&#39;s very good. While the game has yet to receive a proper PS5 upgrade, the extra grunt of Sony&#39;s next-gen console does allow the game to finally run at a locked 60fps — something the PS4 Pro couldn&#39;t handle.</p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-games-for-ps5-playstation-5-171511880.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-games-for-ps5-playstation-5-171511880.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 452d6729-f136-475c-9bc5-58f8e0ebcc64</guid><dc:creator>恩杰特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:15:05 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691496906</ingested><modified> 2023-08-08T12:15:19+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Engadget]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-05/eac9b330-b196-11eb-b4ff-59c9dcad62e5" width="1800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2021-05/eac9b330-b196-11eb-b4ff-59c9dcad62e5" width="1800"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[The best PS5 games for 2023]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[How to take a screenshot on a Mac]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Taking a screenshot comes in handy for multiple reasons, which is why it&#39;s so easy to do on several devices, including <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-macbook-140032524.html">Macs</a> . When it comes to saving what&#39;s on your display, the answer lies in your keyboard. All you need to remember are a few keyboard shortcuts and you&#39;ll be able to take a screenshot on Mac easily — and there are even ways to save only portions of your display and <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/how-to-screen-record-on-iphone-123016561.html">screen record</a> , too. Here are all of the ways to take a screenshot on a MacBook or Mac desktop.</p><h2> How to take a screenshot of your entire screen</h2><p> If you just want a screenshot of your entire screen, just press: Command (⌘), Shift and 3. By default, that image will appear on your desktop for easy access. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/ec8479e0-351e-11ee-afef-a641eb832293" style="height:900px;width:1600px;" alt="如何在 Mac 上截取屏幕截图" data-uuid="116fa9c6-7029-3a88-90b0-29e325b1b4e3"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Julia Mercado / Engadget</div></figure><h2> How to capture a portion of your screen</h2><p> If you want to save a portion of your screen, hit Command + Shift + 4. A crosshair cursor will appear and you can select which part of the screen you want to capture within the gray box.</p><p> If you hold the Spacebar after selecting a portion of the window, then you can move your cursor to choose what part of the screen you want to capture.</p><p> To take a screenshot of an entire window, select Command + Shift + 4, hover over the window in question and then tap the Spacebar. A camera icon will appear and the window will turn gray to show it&#39;s selected. Click on the screen and you will get an image of the window you chose. (Select option (⌥) in order to get rid of any border edges.)</p><h2> How to customize your screenshot experience</h2><p> If you can&#39;t remember the keys to screenshot an entire window or a certain portion, Macs have an even easier way to screenshot. Press Command + Shift + 5 to bring up the toolbar (or simply open the screenshot tool from Spotlight). </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/1ff12620-351f-11ee-bfdb-bd2d977df68b" style="height:879px;width:1164px;" alt="如何在 Mac 上截取屏幕截图" data-uuid="c422c66c-cb57-3c26-bfe8-afa0c3d6972a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Julia Mercado / Engadget</div></figure><p> This will give you several options, such as taking screenshots of videos and even recording the screen. For a more customized experience, click on Options in order to set a timer for your screenshot and select the folder in which you want to save the image or video. This toolbar also allows you to do the basics like take a screenshot of the entire screen or just a specific window.</p><h2> A bonus for Touch Bar MacBooks </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/40b1b370-351f-11ee-a6ff-21c6bf76ac56" style="height:900px;width:1600px;" alt="如何在 Mac 上截取屏幕截图" data-uuid="51cb11d6-2d52-3517-8e61-feb47d75a299"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Julia Mercado / Engadget</div></figure><p> MacBooks with a Touch Bar have the ability to screenshot the bar itself: hit Command + Shift + 6 to do so.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/how-to-take-a-screenshot-on-mac-120034155.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/how-to-take-a-screenshot-on-mac-120034155.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> fab30fda-f913-4452-9a1e-c1268d4fa57b</guid><dc:creator> Julia Mercado</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:00:34 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691439548</ingested><modified> 2023-08-07T20:19:18+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Julia Mercado]]></category><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/af663ae0-0881-11ee-bd5a-9589405fcff0" width="2400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/af663ae0-0881-11ee-bd5a-9589405fcff0" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Nathan Ingraham / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Apple MacBook Air (15-inch, M2)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Apple MacBook Air (15-inch, M2)]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Morning After: Elon Musk says a medical issue may postpone his cage match]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Here&#39;s a series of words that&#39;ll send any sane person sighing themselves into oblivion. ( Sorry in advance.) Elon Musk has announced he may need to postpone his potential brawl with Mark Zuckerberg over a medical issue. The Xitter owner Xeeted he <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/elon-musk-says-he-might-need-surgery-before-any-